OL,3,CWhy are thousands of prisoners to be
OL,4,Creleased early from UK jails?
OL,6,FTo free up space in prisons, the
OL,7,Fgovernment announced in July that some
OL,8,Fprisoners would be released after
OL,9,Fserving only 40% of their sentence
OL,10,Frather than 50% - as required under
OL,11,Fprevious guidelines.
OL,13,FThe first set of prisoners to be
OL,14,Freleased on Tuesday are those who were
OL,15,Fgiven sentences of five years or less.
OL,17,FThere are exceptions, however. Those
OL,18,Fserving sentences for sex and violent
OL,19,Foffences are excluded, as are some
OL,20,Foffences related to domestic violence.
